p: Overall, 30 EO constituents, or 99.0% of the total oil content were found in the Greek laurel EO ( Table 2). Fourteen of the EO constituents were with concentrations above 1%. The main EO constituents were: 1,8-cineole (30.8%), α-terpinyl acetate (14.9%), α-terpineol (8.0%), sabinene (7.9%), terpinen-4-ol (6.0%), α-pinene (5.3%), β-pinene (3.6%), methyleugenol (3.6%), and γ-terpinene (3.3%).
